<div id="review_1490509" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1490509" />
    <a title="Lucy " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/45923-lucy"><img alt="Lucy " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1300985055p2/45923.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1490509?book_show_action=true">May 28, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lucy " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lucy " href="/user/show/45923-lucy">Lucy </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/45923-lucy?shelf=teen">teen</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1490509" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2185998561365594017">Lauren Smith&apos;s mom left when she was six. Her dad, a distant figure in her life, is rarely there for her. Meanwhile, Lauren is dating perfect Dave. Dave is popular, gorgeous, and actually a decent human being. He&apos;s good and kind and he loves her, and any girl would kill to be his girlfriend. So why is Lauren so unhappy? It takes the arrival of Evan Kirkland, a guy from her distant past, to wake Lauren up. With Evan, she feels different. It&apos;s not just that Evan excites her - when she&apos;s with Evan,</span>
  <span id="freeText2185998561365594017" style="display:none">Lauren Smith's mom left when she was six. Her dad, a distant figure in her life, is rarely there for her. Meanwhile, Lauren is dating perfect Dave. Dave is popular, gorgeous, and actually a decent human being. He's good and kind and he loves her, and any girl would kill to be his girlfriend. So why is Lauren so unhappy? It takes the arrival of Evan Kirkland, a guy from her distant past, to wake Lauren up. With Evan, she feels different. It's not just that Evan excites her - when she's with Evan, she starts to feel more and more like herself. As Dave starts to make plans for their future together, Lauren must decide who she really wants to be.<br /><br />The writing in this book is gorgeous. Lauren's voice is strong and distictive and achingly real. Her inner struggle, her family life and her friendships, all feel like they could be happening to your best friend. The female characters in the book are really strong. Lauren herself, her best friend Katie (who could have been a one-note character but is remarkably multidimensional), but new friend Gail - all of them are alive and real and almost tangible. Unfortunately, the guys feel like one-dimensional props. We barely get to know Perfect Dave. And even as Lauren is fascinated and compelled to spend time with Evan, we never really see what the appeal is, and what Evan is really like.<br /><br />Great YA voice, with some less than stellar characterisation of anyone male.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2185998561365594017" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


